excerpt: Coonoor is a hill station in the southern Indian state of Tamil Nadu. It’s known for its tea estates in the surrounding Nilgiri hills. Sim’s Park is a sprawling public garden with plants like rhododendrons, roses and eucalyptus trees. The steam Nilgiri Mountain Railway travels between the towns of Mettupalayam and Ooty via Coonoor. Dolphin’s Nose is a vantage point with views of the cascading Catherine Falls.
detail_description: Coonoor, a charming hill station in Tamil Nadu, is renowned for its picturesque tea estates nestled in the Nilgiri hills. The town boasts Sim’s Park, an expansive public garden featuring a diverse array of flora such as rhododendrons and eucalyptus trees. Visitors can also experience the scenic Nilgiri Mountain Railway that connects Coonoor with Mettupalayam and Ooty.
name: Coonoor
address: Tamil Nadu, India

detail_description: C.S.I All Saints' Church in Coonoor is a stunning example of colonial architecture, boasting a Gothic-style layout and elegant stained glass windows. Built with British assistance in the 19th century, this Anglican church exudes historical significance. The interior is adorned with intricate wooden carvings that are over 160 years old, creating a serene and holy atmosphere for visitors.
name: C.S.I All Saints' Church

excerpt: Circa-1908 railway for steam locomotives, extending 28.5 miles with sweeping views & a steep rise.
detail_description: The Nilgiri Mountain Railway Line, built in 1908, is a picturesque steam locomotive railway extending 28.5 miles through the stunning Nilgiri hills from Mettupalayam to Ooty, passing through Coonoor town. The journey offers sweeping views and a steep rise as it slowly scales an elevation of 326 meters to 2023 meters over a span of five hours. This historic railway has notable connections to early photographers and influential figures buried along its route.
name: Nilgiri Mountain Railway Line
address: Tamil Nadu, India

The broken statue of a mourning angel adds to the eerie atmosphere of this remote location amidst mist-covered hills.

detail_description: The Pasteur Institute of India, established in 1907 near Sims Park, is renowned for its contributions to vaccinology. Originally founded by the British government for vaccine production, it has evolved into one of Tamil Nadu's premier research institutes. The institute offers academic courses and training programs while also operating a dispensary and producing vaccines for rabies, tetanus, and diphtheria. It is an important hospital for dog bites and provides treatment even for rabies-infected cases.
name: Pasteur Institute of India
